The target for the primary balance excluding grants (measured from below the line) was met by a margin of $\operatorname{ECS}7.4$ million (0.4 percent of GDP);   
Domestic arrears older than 60 days were reduced by more than EC\$ 10 million during the first half of this year, meeting the end-June target by a margin of $\operatorname{ECS}0.7$ million (0.04 percent of GDP);   
No new external loans were contracted and no external arrears were accumulated through end-June.

